radiographic_examinations.findings: The lung bases are clear. The appendix is dilated measuring up to 9 mm in width with minimal adjacent fat stranding and hyperemia. No oral contrast is seen within the appendix. Several likely reactive adjacent lymph nodes. Distal loops of large bowel and rectum are of normal size. The uterus and bilateral adnexa appear normal. Trace amount of pelvic free fluid. No free air or abscess formation. No concerning osseous lesion.
